text: Nassarius hanraveni is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. ==Description== The length of the shell varies between 4.5 mm and 6.5 mm. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off Borneo and Java. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 2006
title: Nassarius hanraveni
